                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename>, the abbot</persName>, and the <orgName key="org_103001">convent of Kyrkestall</orgName> 
                  confirm to <persName>
                           <forename>Reiner</forename> de <surname>Pontefr[act]</surname>
                        </persName>
                  and his heirs their messuage in <placeName key="place_103312">Pontefract</placeName> which <persName>sir 
                     <forename>Robt.</forename> de <surname>Laci</surname>
                        </persName> gave them for
                  an inn ("pro hospicio habendo"), paying annually one stone of wax at the Assumption B. M. V., 
                  the light at the altar of the church; reserving the use of the house for their "hospicium" when they visit the place.
                  (<origDate notBefore="1182" notAfter="1190" precision="low">c. 1182-1190</origDate>.) 
                  . </p>
